 Here is a function called `checkPrimeInArray` that takes an input array of five numbers and checks if any of them are prime. If a prime number is found, it will be printed to the console using `console.log`. Please note that for better accuracy, this function uses a simplified version of the trial division method that checks only up to the square root of the number. In real-world use, you may want to consider more efficient algorithms, such as the Sieve of Eratosthenes or the Miller-Rabin primality test, if performance is a concern or for larger input ranges.

